Function: f : R3
          x_i E argmin f(x_1,...,x_{i-1}, eta, x_{i+1},...,xn)

a) Jacobi's Method terminates when alpha = 1/n.

       f(x) = f(x+alpha*(x_bar-x))

            = f(x+(x_bar-x)/n)
 
            = f(x)

b) x never minimizes at all forms of f, especially when alpha = 1/n. 

   If f(x) = sum_j=i_J[ f_j*(sum_i=1_n[ a_ji *x_i ]) ]
   
           = sum_j=i_J[ f_j*(sum_i=1_n[ a_ji *x_i*+(x_bar-x_i)/n ]) ]

           = sum_j=i_j[ f_j*(sum_i=1_n[ a_ji *x_i]) ]

           != f(x*)
 
 
